description:
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span&gt;Child &amp; Adolescent Psychotherapist, Band 7&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Greenwich CAMHS Adolescent Team&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Full time: 37.50 hours per week&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Permanent&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a fantastic new opportunity for an enthusiastic and dynamic Child &amp; Adolescent Psychotherapist to join a highly specialist service for children, young people and their families and carers in the Royal Borough of Greenwich.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Greenwich CAMHS multidisciplinary &amp; Adolescent Team offer young people and their families an intensive, outreach, community based treatment. The team works closely with its multi-agency colleagues.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Band 7 Child &amp; Adolescent Psychotherapist will join the fulltime band 8a Child &amp; Adolescent Psychotherapist to ensure psychoanalytic based treatments are available to young people.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Child &amp; Adolescent Psychotherapy team in Oxleas NHS Foundation Trust is an established, active, diverse group that meets regularly, runs a journal club, holds an annual conference and welcomes innovatory ideas and collaborations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Oxleas Trust has consistently achieved high ratings in quality assessments, patient and staff surveys with a culture of supporting staff whilst providing excellent services within a robust clinical governance framework.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Oxleas NHS Foundation Trust operates a Probationary Period, further details are available on request.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Greenwich CAMHS – 020 3260 5211 and speak to Olivia Thompson or Laura Talbot.&lt;/p&gt;
